doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    meta(charset="UTF-8")
    meta(name="viewport", content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0")
    title Classic Mocha Recipe
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='/stylesheets/navbar.css') 
    link(rel="stylesheet", href="/stylesheets/recipe1.css")
  
  body
    include layout.jade 
    header
      h1 Classic Mocha
      
    section.recipe-preview
      .recipe-img-container
        img(src='/images/recipe1.png', alt='Classic Mocha', class='recipe-image')
      .recipe-info
        h2 The Perfect Blend of Espresso & Chocolate
        p This classic mocha recipe combines rich chocolate with freshly brewed espresso for a comforting and delicious drink.

    section.recipe-history
      h2 History of Mocha
      p The mocha coffee originated from the city of Mocha in Yemen, where coffee beans were first traded. The modern mocha recipe blends espresso and chocolate, which became popular as a sweet variation of the traditional coffee. Today, it's loved globally for its smooth texture and rich taste.

    section.recipe-details
      h2 Ingredients and Instructions
      .details-container
        .ingredients
          h2 Ingredients
          ul
            li 1 cup of brewed espresso
            li 1 cup of milk
            li 2 tablespoons of cocoa powder
            li 2 tablespoons of sugar (or to taste)
            li Whipped cream (optional)

        .instructions
          h2 Instructions
          ol
            li Brew espresso and set aside.
            li In a saucepan, heat milk and cocoa powder until warm and mixed.
            li Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
            li Pour espresso into a mug, top with the chocolate milk, and finish with whipped cream if desired.

    footer.footer
      p Discover more coffee recipes on our website.
